  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    org.dblp.mmdb.FieldReader.getAttributes(int)
    Use Field.getAttributes() for same result.
    org.dblp.mmdb.PersonName.getName()
    Use PersonName.name() instead.
    org.dblp.mmdb.FieldReader.getNumberOfFields()
    Use FieldReader.numberOfFields() for same result.
    org.dblp.mmdb.FieldReader.getTag(int)
    Use Field.tag() for same result. Instead of 
     for( int i=0; i < getNumberOfFields(); i++ ) {
     if getTag(i).equals(tag) {
        ...
     }
 }
    idiom, use FieldReader.getFields(String[]) or FieldReader.fields(String[]).
    org.dblp.mmdb.FieldReader.getValue(int)
    Use Field.value() for the same result.

    Instead of the 

     for( int i=0; i < getNumberOfFields(); i++ ) {
     if getTag(i).equals(tag) {
        ...
     }
 }
    idiom, use FieldReader.getFields(String[]) or FieldReader.fields(String[]).
    org.dblp.mmdb.FieldReader.hasAttribute(int)
    Use Field.attribute(String) for same result.
    org.dblp.mmdb.FieldReader.indexOf(String)
    Use of tag numbers is discontinued.

    Instead of the 

     for( int i=0; i < getNumberOfFields(); i++ ) {
     if getTag(i).equals(tag) {
        ...
     }
 }</pre> idiom, use {@link #getFields(String[])} or {@link #fields(String[])}.
             <p>
             Instead of the <pre>
 if( indexOf(tag) >= 0) {
    ...
 }
    idiom, use FieldReader.contains(String).
    org.dblp.mmdb.FieldReader.indexOf(String, int)
    Use of tag numbers is discontinued.

    Instead of the 

     int index = fields.indexOf(tag);
 while (index > -1) {
     ...
     index = fields.indexOf(tag, index + 1);
 }
    idiom, use FieldReader.getFields(String[]) or FieldReader.fields(String[]).

    Instead of the 

     if( indexOf(tag) >= 0) {
    ...
 }
    idiom, use FieldReader.contains(String).
